notesStmt.note: First 30 folios are much damaged, with partly illegible text.
Defective at the beginning, and some leaves are also missing after folio 48.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 14; written lines: 14; Uniform layout. Visible pen ruling. Initial words written in larger characters, often enclosed in a pen and ink designs Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Sefardi (?) square script of the 15th century. Partially punctuated.

binding.p: Post-1600. Black leather. Spine: 'Siddur, Roman Use. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 26,971.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Giuseppe Almanzi (b. 1801, d. 1860), bibliophile; his manuscript no. 82: his library including 322 medieval Hebrew manuscripts were purchased en bloc by the British Museum in October 1865 for Â£1,000 through Asher & Co., Berlin dealer to the British Museum (see 131-153: inscribed, [183v].
